inter|emit || thebis | relic||tis ad|uenit
taren|t(um) ubi a || danis|ta im||puris|simo
coac|tor con|ductust || quaestum | bon(o) ani|mo c(um) oc|cipit


emit|titur || qui fae|nus pos||cat iniquom




--------------------------------------------------------------

ibi a danista impurissimo coactor conductus est.

where he seeks employment
as coactor to forget his crimes away from death
and with a decent wage. He enters the service of
a bad moneylender whose clients Hercules must chase
and recover payments from.

---------------------------------------------------------
There he makes a big
impression with his job-adequate physique and his efficiency.

Quaestus ei satis placet.
(it doesn't involve death but rather money (mercede) and food)

He himself likes the job largely ignoring the bad aspects
of it.

------------------------------------------------------------

One of these clients is a young guy who took a
loan in his father's absence to help a poor girl he fell in
love with pay for her mother's funeral.

patre apsente adulescens amans grandi fenore
argumentum ab danista sumpsit ut uirginem
egentem adiutet funus matris

cum hercules coactor faenus poscit
nec habet quod det
acriter pugnatur

-------------------------------------------------------------

herculem deludit dissuadetque
mora

deinde amorem cum riuali

uirginem cum coram incusat
repudiat negatque se eum umquam nouisse

is censet eam insanisse
mori cupis
cum hercules feneratorem poscit rogat ut potius se interemet


He fights off Hercules
with success initially but when he discovers his love interest with a
rival and after being subsequently rejected by her when he
confronts her, he gives up and plead Hercules to finish him off.




-----------------------------------------------------------
Hercules refuses and decides to avenge his newfound comrade
putting justice before his duty again.

tum se negat umquam id facturum hercules
uero nouos sodalis adiutare institit

-----------------------------------------------------------
While fighting is building up in epic proportion, the rival
flees to the girl house and exceeded the old servant of
the girls speaks up as a negociator.

iam instat proelium
iam impendit proelium
iam appropinquat proelium

riualis ad amicam refugium petit

-----------------------------------------------------------
the girl is discovered
to have a twin sister and the two sisters to be Hercules' daughters.

reperitur uirginem habere sororem geminam
ambaeque esse herculis filiae

--------------------------------------------------------------------

Subsequently the moneylender is punished for his heartless behavior
and the father of the boys consent to the marriage

danista
hercules filias spondet cum dote
patres adulescentum

-------------------------------------------------------------------
